.SH "NAME"
gitcommitizen \- configuration file for conventional commit linting
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
\fB.gitcommitizen\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
The \fB.gitcommitizen\fP file defines commit message types and scopes for validating conventional commits.
It allows specifying global scopes, type\-specific scopes, and exceptions to ensure consistent commit messages.
.SH "FILE FORMAT"
.sp
Each line is pipe\-delimited:
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
<type>|<description>|<scope>[,<scope>]...
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
\fBtype\fP
.RS 4
Commit type (e.g., \f(CRfeat\fP, \f(CRfix\fP).
.RE
.sp
\fBdescription\fP
.RS 4
Human\-readable description of the type.
.RE
.sp
\fBscopes\fP
.RS 4
Comma\-separated list of scopes with optional prefixes.
Types inherit all global scopes by default. Use prefixes to modify:
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
\f(CRscope\fP or \f(CR+scope\fP adds to inherited scopes
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
\f(CR\-scope\fP removes from inherited scopes
.RE
.RE
.sp
Global scopes are defined with \f(CR*\fP as the type:
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
*|<description>|<scope>[,<scope>]...
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
The last definition of a type takes precedence.
.SH "SYNTAX"
.sp
Lines starting with \f(CR#\fP are comments. Blank lines are ignored.
.SH "EXAMPLES"
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
# Global scopes available to all types
*||api,core

# Types with descriptions and scope overrides
feat|A new feature|ui
fix|A bug fix|
docs|Documentation changes|\-api
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.SH "FILE LOCATION"
.sp
Place \fB.gitcommitizen\fP in the root of a Git repository.
.SH "NOTES"
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Types are lowercase identifiers (e.g., \f(CRfeat\fP, \f(CRfix\fP).
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Scopes may include letters, numbers, dashes, underscores, and \f(CR@\fP (e.g., \f(CR@types/node\fP).
.RE
